ECUADOR: Ecuador's crude price rises to $18.85 per barrel.Ecuador's crude price rises to $18.85 per barrel.The reference price of Ecuador's crude rose to an average $18.85 per barrel on August 14, up from the $18.65 registered the day before, a spokesman for the state-run Petroecuador oil company said Tuesday.The price is tied to the Alaska North Slope (USG) and Oman crude prices, with different discounts payable in 30 days.The price average in July was 17.46 per barrel, while in July 1995 was $14.13 per barrel.Ecuador withdrew from the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) in December 1992.-- Gustavo Oviedo, Quito Newsroom, 5932 258 433